                                         JOHANNESBURG - The Basic Education Department is investigating a teacher accused of raping a 14-year-old in Limpopo. It’s understood the 51-year-old teacher offered the teenager a lift home from school on Friday and attacked her. The suspect was arrested just a few hours later. Spokesman Sam Makondo said: “The department views this matter in a very, very serious light. And it’s emphatic that if there is any wrongdoing, there should be consequences.”